You are here:

View, Collaborate, and Take Action from Einstein CRM Analytics
Converse with Your Data
Ask data questions using non-technical language, and view answers in automatically configured charts.
Save Your Filtered View of a Dashboard
No need to reselect the filters every time you open a dashboard because you don’t have permission to save the selections permanently. Change the filters and save your own view. Only you can see your views—other users still see the original dashboards.

Tableau Views in CRM Analytics
Gain insights on Tableau Cloud and Tableau Server data from the comfort of CRM Analytics Home.
Control Who Sees What in an App with Asset Visibility
App Managers and Editors can use the Asset Visibility feature to control the visibility of select assets. Assets remain visible to app Managers and Editors regardless of the asset’s status.

Collaborate with Dashboard Annotations
Annotate dashboard widgets with comments posted in the dashboard and in Chatter.
Present Live, Interactive Dashboards
Conduct meetings directly from CRM Analytics by presenting dashboards in running apps.

Share Dashboards, Widgets, and Lenses
Share a dashboard, widget, or lens with your colleagues by posting it to Chatter or copying its unique URL.

Download CRM Analytics Images and Export Filtered Data
Extract detailed insights from CRM Analytics that support collaboration and informed decision-making.
Create PDF Files and Print Your Dashboards
Dashboards are printer-friendly, and you can print or save PDF files of dashboards from your browser.

Post CRM Analytics Dashboards and Lenses to Slack
Facilitate data-driven collaboration by sharing directly from CRM Analytics to your channels in Slack.
Perform Salesforce Actions Directly from CRM Analytics
Take action on your insights directly from CRM Analytics. Perform custom and mass quick actions from charts and tables in lenses and dashboards.
title: View, Collaborate, and Take Action with Einstein CRM Analytics
